A typeahead is three reactive steps glued together: `debounceTime` waits for the keystroke stream to go quiet (300 ms is a good default), `distinctUntilChanged` drops consecutive duplicates so backspacing to the same term doesn't refetch, and `switchMap` cancels any pending HTTP request the moment a newer query arrives. Using `mergeMap` here would produce races where a slow earlier request resolves after a newer one and overwrites fresher results.

