The classic shape is an `interval` emitting a ticking cadence, gated by the latest value of a `BehaviorSubject<boolean>` read via `withLatestFrom`. Since `BehaviorSubject` always has a current value, the gate is synchronous — no race on startup. When the user pauses, the filter simply drops ticks; the outer subscription remains live, so flipping back to true resumes immediately without reconnecting.

